Sure. I have an indexed  field called ‚Äúobject_name‚Äù. There may be multiple points stored that have the same ‚Äúobject_name‚Äù field. I want to get all the points that match the object name, average their vector and then get similar points to the average vector.

To do this I am doing it in two steps. First do a scroll with the ‚Äúobject_name‚Äù:

```
POST /collections/{collection_name}/points/scroll

{
    "filter": {
        "must": [
            { "key": "object_name", "match": { "value": "object_1" } },
        ]
    }
}
```

Then use the ids of the points returned in the positive field with the recommendation search:

```
POST /collections/{collection_name}/points/recommend
{
  "positive": [15, 27, 38],
  "filter": {
        "must_not": [
            {
                "key": "object_name",
                "match": {
                    "value": "object_1"
                }
            }
        ]
  },
  "strategy": "average_vector",
  "limit": 10

}
```

